Rating: 3
I used boneless breasts dredged in seasoned flour (having flattened them a bit because they were very plump), and added diced red pepper. Also added some butter before returning them to the pan, and after flipping them I cut off the gas and let them finish cooking on residual heat. They came out very moist and the sauce was surprisingly good. I don't love it enough for a company-type special meal, but for something easy with ingredients I generally have on hand it's a keeper.

