Rating: 2
This came out flavorful but dry. I think I'd like to experiment with coating the chicken in flour beforehand, adding the prosciutto and sage at the last minute to maintain the integrity of their texture and color, substituting unsalted chicken broth for some of the wine, and thickening the sauce somehow. Watch out for hidden sources of salt with this dish (adding extra prosciutto, substituting cooking wine, salting the chicken, using salted chicken broth), because the recipe already borders upon too salty. I definitely needed a bland grain as accompaniment.

