Rating: 3
Very tasty! Even though I did not salt the chicken, the dish came out too salty because I did the unspeakable and used white cooking wine, which contains some salt. Be sure to use regular white wine because the prosciutto contains enough salt for the entire dish. Because I had trouble mixing in the sage evenly once the chicken was in the skillet, next time I will mix in the wine, prosciutto, and sage just before I add the chicken. Maybe using a Dutch oven instead of a skillet would have made mixing easier. And yes, wild rice would have been a great balance for my slightly-salty version of this dish. I do agree with the reviewer who said that the colors faded greatly during cooking, but it still tasted excellent.

