Rating: 4
This is a delicious, easy recipe! It's also pretty healthy -- I paired it with a long grain & wild rice mix and steamed asparagus, along with a dry chardonnay -- what a great dinner. Definitely suitable for company fare, and even my husband (who doesn't care for "fancy" cooking :) ) loved it. I added a few other herbs the second time I made it; basil, tarragon, and parsley. I also prepare it doubled, using a whole package of chicken breasts, and I halve the amount of white wine called for, subbing chicken broth for the remainder of the liquid. This mix of broth & wine in the sauce was really quite good! I also omitted celery, since we both dislike that. We serve the extra sauce over the chicken and wild rice. What a great recipe! A new "chicken-night" staple for my house.